global_temperatures.about: These data are based on the [Mann surface temperature reconstruction, 500-2009](http://www.ncdc.noaa.gov/paleo/pubs/mann2009b/mann2009b.html). Mann's original paper [Global Signatures and Dynamical Origins of the Little Ice Age and Medieval Climate Anomaly](http://www.meteo.psu.edu/~mann/shared/articles/MannetalScience09.pdf). Mann's data are the temperature anomalies from the 30 year global average from 1961 through 1999 of 14.0 degrees C developed by Jones et al, 1999 [SURFACE AIR TEMPERATURE AND ITS CHANGES OVER THE PAST 150 YEARS](http://seaice.apl.washington.edu/Papers/JonesEtal99-SAT150.pdf).
